State of North Carolina ex rel. Commissioner of Insurance
v.
North Carolina Rate Bureau In the Matter of the Filing Dated January 3, 2014 by the North Carolina Rate Bureau for Revised Homeowners' Insurance Rates & Homeowners' Insurance Territory Definitions No. 333P16-2 Supreme Court of North Carolina. February 14, 2017 R. Michael Strickland, Attorney at Law, Marvin M. Spivey, Jr., Attorney at Law, Glenn C. Raynor, Attorney at Law, Raleigh, for The North Carolina Rate Bureau. William M. Trott, Attorney at Law, Raleigh. Sherri L. Hubbard, Attorney at Law, Patricia Ford, for North Carolina Department Of Insurance. Robert Devane Croom, IV, Assistant Attorney General, for State of North Carolina. Jonathan L. Crook, Attorney at Law, Raleigh.

ORDER

Upon consideration of the petition filed on the 20th of January 2017 by N.C. Rate Bureau in this matter for for Reconsideration, the following order was entered and is hereby certified to the North Carolina Court of Appeals:

"Denied by order of the Court in conference, this the 14th of February 2017."
